modules.description: Provides elliptic curve operations for generating keys, signing messages, and verifying signatures using the secp256k1 curve. Works with byte sequences, private and public keys, and digital signatures. Used to secure blockchain transactions and authenticate user identities in cryptographic protocols.

Provides operations for handling elliptic curve keys and signatures, including key generation, serialization, and verification. Works with specific curve types like secp256r1 and key types such as secret and public. Used to generate keypairs, sign messages, and verify signatures in cryptographic protocols.
